Simple Chicken Tortilla Soup

1 tbsp butter
1 tbsp olive oil
1 medium onion, finely diced
salt and pepper
2 cloves garlic, minced
1 tbsp ap flour
2 tbsp fajita seasoning
4 c chicken broth
1 c skim milk
1/2 c salsa
4 c cooked chicken, shredded
14 oz can black beans, drained and rinsed
crushed tortilla chips (optional)
green onions (optional)
grated cheese (optiona)

In a soup pot over medium low heat, melt the butter and olive oil. Add onion, seasoning with salt and pepper. Saute, stirring occasionally, until softened, 5-6 min. Stir in garlic and cook for another minute, stirring constantly. Stir in the flour, stirring constantly, for another minute. Stir in fajita seasonin, then the broth and milk. Add the salsa, chicken and black beans, and stir once more. Bring to a low boil, then reduce to a simmer for 30 min.

Nutrition: serving size: 1/4 recipe
Calories: 259; Total Fat: 7g; Saturated Fat: 2g; Monounsaturated Fat: 3g; Cholesterol: 33mg; Sodium: 428mg; Carbohydrate: 28g; Dietary Fiber: 7g; Sugar: 8g; Protein: 20g Potassium: 756mg; Iron: 10%; Vitamin A: 6%; Vitamin C: 8%; Calcium: 13% 
